def autolabel(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its 
       height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate(
            '{}'.format(height),
            xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
            xytext=(0, 0),
            textcoords="offset points",
            ha='center', va='bottom'
        )

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))
x = np.arange(len(top_10_by_deaths['USA']['cases'].iloc[-30:]))

count = 0
for country in top_10_by_deaths:
    if count < 6:
        ax.plot(
            x, (top_10_by_deaths[country]['cases'].iloc[-30:] /
                top_10_by_deaths[country]['popData2018'].iloc[-30:]) *
            100, label=top_10_by_deaths[country]
            ['countriesAndTerritories'].iloc[0], linewidth=3
        )
    else:
        ax.plot(
            x, (top_10_by_deaths[country]['cases'].iloc[-30:] /
                top_10_by_deaths[country]['popData2018'].iloc[-30:]) *
            100, label=top_10_by_deaths[country]
            ['countriesAndTerritories'].iloc[0], linewidth=3,
            linestyle='dashed'
        )
    count += 1

ax.set(
    ylabel="Percent of Population Infected",
    title="COVID-19 Cases\n(Percent of Population)"
)
ax.set_xticklabels(
    np.arange(min(covid_dates[-30:]), max(covid_dates[-30:]) + one_day,
              step=1), rotation=90
)
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(min(x), max(x) + 1, step=1))

ax.margins(x=0)
ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
plt.legend(loc=2)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

def align_yaxis(ax1, v1, ax2, v2):
    """adjust ax2 ylimit so that v2 in ax2 is aligned to v1 in ax1"""
    _, y1 = ax1.transData.transform((0, v1))
    _, y2 = ax2.transData.transform((0, v2))
    inv = ax2.transData.inverted()
    _, dy = inv.transform((0, 0)) - inv.transform((0, y1-y2))
    miny, maxy = ax2.get_ylim()
    ax2.set_ylim(miny+dy, maxy+dy)


def autolabel(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its 
       height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate(
            f"{height}",
            xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
            xytext=(0, 0),
            textcoords="offset points",
            ha='center', va='bottom'
        )
In [22]:
def plot_county(cname, df, ytick_step):
    """Returns matplotlib plot object for a given county

    Args: cname - the county name, string
          df - the dataframe with the per county data
          ytick_step - int used to adjust yticks"""

    county_df = (
        df[df['county'] == cname].iloc[-30:].sort_values(by=['date'])
    )
    county_tot = (
        df[df['county'] == cname].iloc[-30:].groupby(['county'])['cases']
        .max()[0]
    )
    county_deaths = (
        df[df['county'] == cname].iloc[-30:].groupby(['county'])['deaths']
        .max()[0]
    )

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))
    x = np.arange(len(county_df['date']))

    ax.bar(x, county_df['cases'], label='Cases', width=0.6)
    ax.set(
        xlabel="Days", ylabel="Total Cases",
        title=f"{cname} County COVID-19\nTotal Cases: {county_tot}\n"
        f"Total Deaths: {county_deaths}"
    )
    ax.set_xticklabels(
        np.arange(min(county_df['date']), max(county_df['date']) +
                  datetime.timedelta(days=1), step=1), rotation=90
    )
    ax.set_xticks(np.arange(min(x), max(x) + 1, step=1))
    ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)

    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    ax2.plot(x, county_df['deaths'], label='Deaths', color='r', linewidth=3)
    ax2.set(ylabel='Total Deaths')
    ax2.set_yticks(range(0, max(county_df['deaths']) + 1, ytick_step))

    ax.set_yticks(
        np.linspace(int(ax.get_yticks()[0]), int(ax.get_yticks()[-1]),
                    len(ax2.get_yticks()))
    )

    ax2.grid(b=False)
    h1, l1 = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    h2, l2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
    ax.legend(h1 + h2, l1 + l2, loc=2)

    align_yaxis(ax, 0, ax2, 0)
    ax.margins(x=0)
    plt.tight_layout()

    return plt

Combine DataFrame containing COVID-19 data with DataFrame containing longitude and latitude data

In [31]:
us_counties_df = us_counties_df[
    (us_counties_df['state'] != 'AK') & (us_counties_df['state'] != 'HI')
]

us_counties_grouped_df = (
    us_counties_df.groupby(['county', 'state', 'fips'])
    [['cases', 'deaths']].sum().reset_index(level=[0, 1, 2])
)

us_county_data_geo_df = pd.merge(
    us_counties_grouped_df, counties_gdf, left_on='fips', right_on='FIPS',
    how='left'
)

)

)

    states_gdf[(states_gdf['STATE_NAME'] != 'Alaska') &
               (states_gdf['STATE_NAME'] != 'Hawaii')].iterrows()
):
    ax.annotate(
        s=row['STATE_ABBR'], xy=(row['geometry'].centroid.coords.xy[0][0],
                                 row['geometry'].centroid.coords.xy[1][0]),
        ha='center', color='black'
    )
geo_county_points[geo_county_points['cases'] >= 5000].plot(
    ax=ax, color='r', alpha=0.6, markersize=geo_county_points['cases'] / 500
)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

n_days = 30
y = np.array(
    covid_data_df[covid_data_df['countriesAndTerritories'] ==
                  'USA']['cases'][:n_days+1].diff(periods=-1)[0:-1]
)

x = np.array(
    covid_data_df[covid_data_df['countriesAndTerritories'] == 'USA']
    ['dateRep'][:n_days]
)
z = np.polyfit(np.arange(len(x)), y, 1)
p = np.poly1d(z)(np.arange(len(x)))

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))

ax.set_title("COVID-19 US Cases Diff -1 Day (Last 30 Days)", fontsize=16)
ax.set(ylabel="Diff")
plt.xticks(rotation=90, ha='right', fontsize=14)

ax.bar(x, y, width=0.5, label='New Cases')
ax.plot(x, p, color='r', label='Trend', linewidth=3)

ax.legend(loc=2)
ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
ax.margins(x=0)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
